Since we want the two largest stones each time, and heapq.pop() gives us the smallest each time, we just need to make every value of stones negative at the beginning.
```
import heapq
class Solution:
    def lastStoneWeight(self, stones: List[int]) -> int:
        stones = [-val for val in stones]
        heapq.heapify(stones)
        while len(stones) > 1:
            x1 = heapq.heappop(stones)
            x2 = heapq.heappop(stones)
            if x1 != x2:
                heapq.heappush(stones,x1-x2)
        if len(stones) == 0:
            return 0
        return -stones[0]
```

